Determined to ensure unity and peaceful coexistence in Yobe State, Tikau Emirate Council, Sabon Garin Nangere on Saturday turbaned six Village Heads to serve in various communities. His Royal Highness, Alhaji Mohammed Abubakar Ibn Grema, the Emir of Tikau recently appointed Alhaji Abdullahi Adamu as village head of Tikau, Mohammed Abubakar Ibn Mohammed Abubakar Grema for Sabon Garin Nangere, Alhaji Abdullahi Umar Kukuri, Village Head of Kukuri while Ibrahim Usman as Watinani village head, Garba Wakili, Chukuriwa and Engr. Musa Haruna Challino respectively. The turbaning ceremony was attended by important personalities, Emirs of Fika, Bade, Fune and Jajere. Politicians, Youth and Women organizations, cultural groups, traditional leaders, religious leaders, sons of the Emirate and others are too numerous to mention. Religious, Community Leaders Parley With YSCHMA On Informal… YSCHMA Engages Religious Leaders For Commencement of Informal… In his address shortly after the turbaning, the Waziri of Tikau Emirate, Col. Mohammed A. Abdu (rtd), thanked all that attended the occasion and urged the newly turbaned District Heads to live up to expectations in meeting the yearnings and aspirations of their community members through good leadership. He used the forum to appeal to parents to always send their children to schools in order to improve the enrollment and reduce the number of the out of school children. On his part, the Chairman Nangere Local Government Council, Alhaji Salisu Yerima congratulated the new District Heads and urged them to fully sensitize their subjects on the importance of obtaining Permanent Voters Card (PVC).